---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Navagraha Homam | Planetary Remedy | Nagayakshi Temple">

  <section class="pooja-hero">
    <div class="pooja-hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="pooja-hero-content">
      <span class="pooja-badge">Quarterly Homam</span>
      <h1>Navagraha Homam</h1>
      <p class="pooja-tagline">Sacred fire ritual to pacify the nine planets and remove karmic obstacles</p>
      <div class="pooja-quick-info">
        <div class="quick-info-item">
          <span class="info-label">Frequency</span>
          <span class="info-value">Quarterly</span>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-info-item">
          <span class="info-label">Duration</span>
          <span class="info-value">3&#8211;4 hours</span>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-info-item">
          <span class="info-label">Offering</span>
          <span class="info-value">&#8377;7,000</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="#booking" class="btn-primary-gold">Book This Homam</a>
        <a href="#details" class="btn-secondary-outline">Learn More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pooja-section" id="details">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>What is Navagraha Homam?</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">
          <p class="intro-text">
            Navagraha Homam is a powerful Vedic fire ritual performed to appease the nine planetary
            deities&#8212;Surya, Chandra, Mangala, Budha, Brihaspati, Shukra, Shani, Rahu, and Ketu.
            The positions of these planets at the time of birth profoundly influence every aspect of
            life, and adverse placements create doshas that manifest as obstacles, health issues,
            and relationship difficulties.
          </p>
          <h3>The Nine Planets &amp; Their Influence</h3>
          <div class="variant-cards">
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>Surya, Chandra &amp; Mangala</h4>
              <p>Sun governs authority, health, and vitality. Moon controls emotions and mental peace.
              Mars rules courage, energy, and property matters. Imbalances cause health deterioration,
              emotional instability, and land disputes.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>Budha, Brihaspati &amp; Shukra</h4>
              <p>Mercury governs communication, business, and intellect. Jupiter rules wisdom, progeny,
              and spiritual growth. Venus controls marriage, relationships, and wealth. Weak placements
              affect these areas adversely.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>Shani, Rahu &amp; Ketu</h4>
              <p>Saturn governs karma, discipline, and longevity. Rahu and Ketu are shadow planets
              creating Sarpa and Kala Sarpa doshas. These three are the most powerful sources of
              karmic obstacles and life disruptions.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="info-box">
            <h4>Quick Facts</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Performed quarterly at auspicious times</li>
              <li>All 9 planets propitiated together</li>
              <li>Specific mantras for each graha</li>
              <li>Homam with nine sacred woods</li>
              <li>Conducted by Ambotti Thampuran</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="info-box highlight">
            <h4>Benefits</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Planetary dosha relief</li>
              <li>Career advancement</li>
              <li>Health improvement</li>
              <li>Relationship harmony</li>
              <li>Mental peace &amp; clarity</li>
              <li>Overall life balance</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tradition-section">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Sacred Origins</span>
        <h2>The Vedic Basis</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="tradition-story">
        <div class="story-image">
          <img src="/images/Navagraha%20Homam.jpg" alt="Navagraha Homam ritual fire">
        </div>
        <div class="story-content">
          <h3>Fire as the Divine Intermediary</h3>
          <p>
            In Vedic tradition, Agni&#8212;the sacred fire&#8212;is considered the messenger between
            the human and divine realms. The Navagraha Homam channels offerings through Agni directly
            to the nine planetary deities, seeking their grace and pacification of malefic influences.
          </p>
          <p>
            The ritual uses nine specific sacred woods (samidha), nine types of grains, and nine
            varieties of flowers corresponding to each planet. Special mantras from the Rigveda and
            Yajurveda are chanted for each graha in sequence, systematically addressing all planetary
            imbalances in one comprehensive ceremony.
          </p>
          <div class="scripture-quote">
            <p>
              &#8220;One who performs the Navagraha Homa with devotion shall be freed from all
              planetary afflictions, and the nine planets shall bestow their grace abundantly.&#8221;
            </p>
            <span class="quote-attribution">&#8212; Brihat Parasara Hora Sastra</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tradition-variants">
        <h3>How the Ritual Addresses Specific Doshas</h3>
        <div class="variant-detail">
          <h4>Shani Dosha (Saturn Affliction)</h4>
          <p>Saturn's adverse placement causes prolonged delays, health issues, financial setbacks,
          and career obstacles. The Shani component of the homam involves sesame seeds, iron offerings,
          and specific Shani mantras to reduce the planet's malefic influence and invoke its disciplined blessings.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="variant-detail">
          <h4>Rahu&#8211;Ketu Dosha</h4>
          <p>Rahu and Ketu create the feared Kala Sarpa and Sarpa Doshas. Their afflictions manifest
          as sudden losses, inexplicable misfortunes, and spiritual disturbances. The Rahu-Ketu segment
          of the homam works in conjunction with the temple's primary Naga worship tradition,
          making this ceremony particularly potent here.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pooja-section audience-section">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Who Should Perform Navagraha Homam?</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">Particularly beneficial for those experiencing these life situations</p>
      </div>
      <div class="audience-grid">
        <div class="audience-card">
          <div class="audience-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><rect x="2" y="7" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M16 7V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2h-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v2"/><line x1="12" y1="12" x2="12" y2="16"/><line x1="10" y1="14" x2="14" y2="14"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Career Obstacles</h3>
          <p>Repeated job loss, promotions blocked, business failures despite sincere effort — often rooted in planetary afflictions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <div class="audience-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M22 12h-4l-3 9L9 3l-3 9H2"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Chronic Health Issues</h3>
          <p>Long-standing unexplained health problems that do not respond fully to medical treatment often have planetary roots.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <div class="audience-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M20.84 4.61a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 0L12 5.67l-1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 7.78l1.06 1.06L12 21.23l7.78-7.78 1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0 0-7.78z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Delayed Marriage</h3>
          <p>Venus and Jupiter afflictions are common causes of marriage delays. Navagraha Homam addresses both simultaneously.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <div class="audience-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M12 2v20M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 0 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 7H6"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Financial Instability</h3>
          <p>Persistent debt, unexpected losses, inability to save despite earning — Mercury, Jupiter, and Saturn doshas are often responsible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <div class="audience-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="5"/><line x1="12" y1="1" x2="12" y2="3"/><line x1="12" y1="21" x2="12" y2="23"/><line x1="4.22" y1="4.22" x2="5.64" y2="5.64"/><line x1="18.36" y1="18.36" x2="19.78" y2="19.78"/><line x1="1" y1="12" x2="3" y2="12"/><line x1="21" y1="12" x2="23" y2="12"/><line x1="4.22" y1="19.78" x2="5.64" y2="18.36"/><line x1="18.36" y1="5.64" x2="19.78" y2="4.22"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Sade Sati Period</h3>
          <p>Those undergoing the 7.5-year Saturn transit (Sade Sati) or Ashtama Shani benefit greatly from regular homam during this period.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <div class="audience-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Progeny Seekers</h3>
          <p>Jupiter rules children and progeny. Weak Jupiter combined with Rahu affliction is a common cause of childlessness.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pricing-section">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Homam Offering</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="pricing-grid single">
        <div class="price-card featured">
          <div class="price-header">
            <h3>Navagraha Homam</h3>
            <div class="price-amount">
              <span class="currency">&#8377;</span>
              <span class="amount">7,000</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="price-features">
            <h4>Includes:</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Homam for all nine planetary deities</li>
              <li>Nine sacred woods &amp; specific samidha</li>
              <li>Rigveda &amp; Yajurveda mantra chanting</li>
              <li>Nine grain &amp; flower offerings</li>
              <li>Graha Shanti pooja after homam</li>
              <li>Prasadam with ash (vibhuti) from homam fire</li>
              <li>Personal sankalpa with your birth details</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <a href="#booking" class="price-cta">Book Now &#8212; &#8377;7,000</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pricing-note">
        <p><strong>Note:</strong> Price includes all ritual materials and priest dakshina.
        Please provide your date, time, and place of birth for accurate sankalpa.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do I need my horoscope / birth chart?</summary>
          <p>Not mandatory, but highly recommended. Providing your date, time, and place of birth allows
          the priest to perform the sankalpa accurately and address specific planetary afflictions in your
          chart. If birth time is unknown, the sankalpa proceeds with available details.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can this be done remotely or must I attend in person?</summary>
          <p>The homam can be performed on your behalf at the temple even if you cannot attend in person.
          You will receive photos/videos during the ceremony and prasadam by post.
          In-person participation is always welcome and recommended if possible.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How often should Navagraha Homam be performed?</summary>
          <p>We perform it quarterly during auspicious planetary periods. For acute doshas (such as Sade
          Sati or Rahu&#8211;Ketu transit), quarterly homam for one full year is recommended. For general
          maintenance, once or twice a year is beneficial.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is this different from Ayilyam Pooja?</summary>
          <p>Yes. Ayilyam Pooja specifically addresses Sarpa/Naga Dosha through serpent deity worship.
          Navagraha Homam addresses the full spectrum of planetary afflictions through fire offerings.
          Both complement each other, and many devotees combine them.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>When is the next scheduled Navagraha Homam?</summary>
          <p>Dates are set quarterly based on astrological auspiciousness. Call the temple at
          +91 9946373522 to confirm the next available date and reserve your slot.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="booking-cta-section" id="booking">
    <div class="booking-cta-container">
      <h2>Book Navagraha Homam</h2>
      <p>Performed quarterly during auspicious planetary periods.<br>
      <strong>Call to confirm next date and reserve your slot.</strong></p>
      <div class="booking-cta-buttons">
        <a href="/register" class="btn-primary-gold btn-large">Book Online</a>
        <a href="tel:+919946373522" class="btn-secondary-outline">Call: +91 9946373522</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
.pooja-hero {
  position: relative;
  min-height: 70vh;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background:
    linear-gradient(rgba(82, 14, 9, 0.75), rgba(82, 14, 9, 0.9)),
    url('/images/Navagraha%20Homam.jpg') center/cover;
  padding: 8rem 2rem 4rem;
  text-align: center;
}
.pooja-hero-overlay { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: radial-gradient(circle at 50% 50%, rgba(212,165,116,0.12) 0%, transparent 60%); }
.pooja-hero-content { max-width: 900px; position: relative; z-index: 10; }
.pooja-badge { display: inline-block; background: var(--laterite-red); color: white; padding: 0.5rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
.pooja-hero h1 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 4.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: white; margin-bottom: 1rem; text-shadow: 0 2px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5); }
.pooja-tagline { font-size: 1.35rem; color: var(--bg-alt); margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.pooja-quick-info { display: flex; gap: 2rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 3rem; padding: 1.8rem 2rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); backdrop-filter: blur(10px); border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2); }
.quick-info-item { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem; }
.info-label { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #ffd285; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; }
.info-value { font-size: 1.15rem; color: white; font-weight: 600; }
.hero-ctas { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.pooja-section { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: var(--bg-base); }
.pooja-section.audience-section { background: var(--bg-alt); }
.pooja-container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; }
.content-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
.content-main { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.9; }
.intro-text { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--laterite-dark); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
.content-main h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.9rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--laterite-red); margin: 2.5rem 0 1.2rem; }
.content-main p { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
.variant-cards { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.2rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
.variant-card { background: var(--bg-alt); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--gold); }
.variant-card h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
.variant-card p { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
.content-sidebar { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem; }
.info-box { background: var(--bg-alt); padding: 1.8rem; border-radius: 10px; border: 2px solid #e8c9a0; }
.info-box.highlight { background: var(--laterite-dark); border-color: var(--gold); }
.info-box h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.info-box.highlight h4 { color: #ffd285; }
.info-box ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
.info-box li { padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem; position: relative; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.05); }
.info-box.highlight li { color: var(--bg-alt); border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }
.info-box li::before { content: '✓'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--laterite-red); font-weight: 700; }
.info-box.highlight li::before { color: var(--gold); }
.tradition-section { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: var(--bg-alt); }
.tradition-story { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 420px 1fr; gap: 3rem; align-items: start; margin: 3rem 0; }
.story-image img { width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.15); filter: sepia(0.15) brightness(0.95); }
.story-content h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.9rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
.story-content p { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.4rem; }
.scripture-quote { background: var(--bg-base); padding: 1.8rem; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 4px solid var(--laterite-red); margin-top: 1.5rem; }
.scripture-quote p { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.25rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--laterite-dark); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
.quote-attribution { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); }
.tradition-variants { margin-top: 4rem; }
.tradition-variants h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 2rem; text-align: center; }
.variant-detail { background: var(--bg-base); padding: 2.5rem; border-radius: 10px; margin-bottom: 1.8rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--gold); }
.variant-detail h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.variant-detail p { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.audience-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 1.8rem; }
.audience-card { background: var(--bg-base); padding: 2rem; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.07); transition: all 0.3s ease; text-align: center; }
.audience-card:hover { transform: translateY(-5px); box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.12); }
.audience-icon { width: 44px; height: 44px; margin: 0 auto 1rem; color: var(--laterite-red); }
.audience-icon svg { width: 100%; height: 100%; }
.audience-card h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.35rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
.audience-card p { font-size: 0.98rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; }
.pricing-section { background: var(--bg-base); padding: 5rem 2rem; }
.pricing-grid.single { display: flex; justify-content: center; }
.pricing-grid.single .price-card { max-width: 500px; width: 100%; }
.price-card { background: var(--bg-base); border-radius: 14px; box-shadow: 0 8px 35px rgba(0,0,0,0.09); overflow: hidden; transition: all 0.3s ease; position: relative; }
.price-card.featured { border: 3px solid var(--gold); }
.price-header { background: var(--laterite-dark); padding: 2.5rem 2rem; text-align: center; color: white; }
.price-card.featured .price-header { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--saffron) 0%, var(--laterite-dark) 100%); }
.price-header h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
.price-amount { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: center; gap: 0.3rem; }
.currency { font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
.amount { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 3.8rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; }
.price-features { padding: 2rem; }
.price-features h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
.price-features ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
.price-features li { padding: 0.7rem 0 0.7rem 1.8rem; position: relative; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bg-alt); }
.price-features li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.price-features li::before { content: '✓'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--laterite-red); font-weight: 700; }
.price-cta { display: block; margin: 0 2rem 2rem; padding: 1.1rem; background: var(--gold); color: var(--text-muted); text-align: center; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; transition: all 0.3s ease; }
.price-cta:hover { background: #e8c9a0; transform: translateY(-2px); }
.pricing-note { max-width: 900px; margin: 2rem auto 0; text-align: center; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 1rem; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-alt); border-radius: 8px; }
.faq-section { background: var(--bg-alt); padding: 5rem 2rem; }
.faq-list { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; }
.faq-item { background: var(--bg-base); margin-bottom: 1.2rem; border-radius: 10px; overflow: hidden; box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.05); }
.faq-item summary { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); padding: 1.4rem 2rem; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; position: relative; }
.faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
.faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; position: absolute; right: 1.5rem; top: 50%; transform: translateY(-50%); font-size: 1.8rem; color: var(--gold-dark); }
.faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '−'; }
.faq-item p { padding: 0 2rem 1.5rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; font-size: 1.02rem; }
